*: {{audio|en-us-abuse-verb.ogg|Audio (US)}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb|abus|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To put to a wrong use; to [[misapply]]; to use [[improperly]]; to [[misuse]]; to use for a wrong purpose or end; to [[pervert]]; as, to '''abuse''' one's authority. {{defdate|from early 15th c.}}
#* ''This principle (if one may so '''abuse''' the word) shoots rapidly into popularity.'' - [[w:James Anthony Froude|James Anthony Froude]]
# {{transitive}} To [[injure]]; to [[maltreat]]; to [[hurt]]; to treat with [[cruelty]].
# {{transitive}} To [[rape]]; to [[assault]]; to [[ravish]]; to [[violate]].{{rfv-sense}}{{rfquote}}
# {{transitive}} To attack with [[coarse]] language; to [[insult]]; to [[revile]].
# {{transitive}} {{obsolete}} To [[deceive]]; to [[trick]]; to [[impose]] on.
#: {{rfdate}} ''Their eyes red and staring, cozened with a moist cloud, and '''abused''' by a double object.'' - Jeremy Taylor

